<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>Analytics for SaaS - ghostanalytics</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Cookieless analytics for SaaS. Follow visitors from landing page to signup and activation, attribute revenue to channels, and skip the consent banner. Powered by ghostanalytics.">
    <meta name="theme-color" content="#0a0c0e">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Geist:wght@400;500;600;700;800&family=Geist+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/marketing.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    @include('site-nav')

    <main>
      <nav class="shell subnav" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span>
        <a href="/use-cases" data-no-router>Use cases</a><span class="sep">/</span>
        <span>SaaS</span>
      </nav>

      <section class="hero shell">
        <div>
          <p class="enter eyebrow">For SaaS</p>
          <h1 class="d1 enter hero-title">From first visit to activated.</h1>
          <p class="d2 enter hero-sub">
            Track the whole SaaS funnel without a cookie banner in the way. See which pages turn visitors into signups, and which channels bring the accounts that stick.
          </p>
          <div class="d3 enter hero-actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/#install">Get your script tag</a>
            <a class="btn ghost" href="/dashboard">See a live dashboard</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="d2 enter panel" aria-label="Sample signup funnel">
          <div class="panel-head">
            <span class="live">Signup funnel, last 30 days</span>
            <span class="panel-tag">Sample data</span>
          </div>
          <svg viewBox="0 0 360 280" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet" role="img" aria-label="A signup funnel narrowing from 8,420 visitors to 612 signups to 289 activated users, a 3.4 percent visitor-to-activated rate" style="display:block;width:100%;height:auto;margin-top:1.1rem">
            <path d="M20,100 L340,100 L286,120 L74,120 Z" fill="#46d3c0" fill-opacity="0.07"></path>
            <path d="M74,164 L286,164 L244,184 L116,184 Z" fill="#46d3c0" fill-opacity="0.07"></path>

            <rect x="20" y="56" width="320" height="44" rx="8" fill="#46d3c0" fill-opacity="0.92"></rect>
            <text x="36" y="84" fill="#04201c" font-family="'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace" font-size="11" letter-spacing="0.8">VISITORS</text>
            <text x="324" y="85" text-anchor="end" fill="#04201c" font-family="'Geist',sans-serif" font-size="19" font-weight="700" letter-spacing="-0.4">8,420</text>

            <rect x="74" y="120" width="212" height="44" rx="8" fill="#46d3c0" fill-opacity="0.58"></rect>
            <text x="90" y="148" fill="#04201c" font-family="'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace" font-size="11" letter-spacing="0.8">SIGNUPS</text>
            <text x="270" y="149" text-anchor="end" fill="#04201c" font-family="'Geist',sans-serif" font-size="18" font-weight="700" letter-spacing="-0.4">612</text>

            <rect x="116" y="184" width="128" height="44" rx="8" fill="#46d3c0" fill-opacity="0.34"></rect>
            <text x="132" y="212" fill="#eef2f3" font-family="'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace" font-size="11" letter-spacing="0.8">ACTIVATED</text>
            <text x="228" y="213" text-anchor="end" fill="#eef2f3" font-family="'Geist',sans-serif" font-size="18" font-weight="700" letter-spacing="-0.4">289</text>

            <line x1="20" y1="250" x2="340" y2="250" stroke="rgba(233,238,240,0.09)"></line>
            <text x="20" y="272" fill="#9aa4a9" font-family="'Geist Mono',ui-monospace,monospace" font-size="11">visitor &#8594; activated</text>
            <text x="340" y="272" text-anchor="end" fill="#46d3c0" font-family="'Geist',sans-serif" font-size="15" font-weight="700">3.4%</text>
          </svg>
        </aside>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="No cookie tax">
        <div class="split">
          <div class="split-text">
            <h3>Measure the funnel without the cookie tax.</h3>
            <p>
              A consent banner costs you the first click and a slice of every measurement behind it. ghostanalytics stores nothing on the visitor, so there is no banner to show and no gap between real signups and counted ones.
            </p>
            <ul class="mini-list">
              <li><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>No cookie prompt between a visitor and your call to action.</li>
              <li><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Every signup counted, not sampled or thresholded away.</li>
              <li><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Pageviews and events flow from the same lightweight script.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <aside class="panel" aria-label="Sample conversion by page">
            <div class="panel-head">
              <span class="live">Signups by landing page</span>
              <span class="panel-tag">Sample data</span>
            </div>
            <div class="top-pages" style="margin-top:1.1rem;">
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path">/pricing</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:100%"></span></span><span class="count">214</span></div>
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path">/</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:62%"></span></span><span class="count">133</span></div>
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path">/integrations</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:38%"></span></span><span class="count">81</span></div>
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path">/blog/launch</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:27%"></span></span><span class="count">58</span></div>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="Channel attribution">
        <div class="rev split">
          <div class="split-text">
            <h3>Prove which channels bring paying users.</h3>
            <p>
              Tag your ads, emails, and partner links with UTM parameters and ghostanalytics carries them through to the signup event. You can tell the difference between a channel that drives traffic and one that drives revenue.
            </p>
            <ul class="mini-list">
              <li><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>UTM source, medium, and campaign on every conversion.</li>
              <li><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>Referrers classified automatically into search, social, and direct.</li>
              <li><span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>One-click GA import, so your history moves with you.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <aside class="panel" aria-label="Sample signups by source">
            <div class="panel-head">
              <span class="live">Signups by source</span>
              <span class="panel-tag">Sample data</span>
            </div>
            <div class="top-pages" style="margin-top:1.1rem;">
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path" style="font-family:var(--sans);">Organic search</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:100%"></span></span><span class="count">188</span></div>
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path" style="font-family:var(--sans);">Product Hunt</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:54%"></span></span><span class="count">102</span></div>
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path" style="font-family:var(--sans);">Newsletter</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:41%"></span></span><span class="count">77</span></div>
              <div class="top-row"><span class="path" style="font-family:var(--sans);">Direct</span><span class="bar"><span style="width:29%"></span></span><span class="count">54</span></div>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-labelledby="saas-track">
        <div class="section-head">
          <h2 id="saas-track" class="section-title">What SaaS teams track.</h2>
          <p class="section-intro">The events that matter for a product-led funnel, each one a single function call.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="qa-grid">
          <div class="qa"><h4>Signup started</h4><p>Fire when the form opens to measure intent, not just completed accounts.</p></div>
          <div class="qa"><h4>Account created</h4><p>Your headline conversion, attributed back to the exact source and campaign.</p></div>
          <div class="qa"><h4>Activated</h4><p>The first real action that predicts retention, tracked as its own goal.</p></div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell-narrow" aria-labelledby="saas-code">
        <div class="section-head">
          <h2 id="saas-code" class="section-title">A conversion is one line.</h2>
          <p class="section-intro">No SDK and no init call. Fire an event from anywhere in your app, with any properties you want to break it down by later.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-grid">
          <div class="code">
            <div class="code-bar"><span>onboarding.ts</span><span>JavaScript</span></div>
            <pre><span class="cmt">// when the account is created</span>
<span class="tok">ghost</span>('signup', { plan: 'pro', source: 'product-hunt' })

<span class="cmt">// later, when they reach the aha moment</span>
<span class="tok">ghost</span>('activated', { plan: 'pro' })</pre>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="code-note">The <code>ghost()</code> function ships with the tracking script, so there is nothing extra to import. Properties become filters and breakdowns in your dashboard, and the beacon <code>POST</code>s to your own <code>/collect</code> endpoint.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="reveal section shell" aria-label="Get started">
        <div class="cta-band">
          <h2>Grow the funnel, not your compliance risk.</h2>
          <div class="cta-actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/#install">Get your script tag</a>
            <a class="btn ghost" href="/use-cases" data-no-router>All use cases</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    @include('site-footer')
  </body>
</html>
